Raw dev notes -- AI-Powered Invoice Processing for an ERP System (March 2026)

Built an invoice processing system for a client. PDFs arrive via email or cloud storage,
get processed by Gemini AI, and output structured files compatible with their ERP import format.
The whole thing runs serverless on Google Apps Script.

Architecture:
- File watcher scans an inbox folder for new invoice PDFs
- Gemini Flash extracts structured data (supplier info, amounts, line items)
- Smart fallback to a larger model when the fast model fails on complex invoices
- Results tracked in a spreadsheet with status management
- Export files generated in the ERP's required format
- Customer-facing web dashboard with Hebrew UI

Key challenges:
- Multi-invoice PDFs: had to split, extract unique invoice numbers, merge duplicates
- Hebrew text and RTL rendering in the dashboard
- Company ID validation with strict format requirements
- AI hallucinating dates -- added dynamic validation ranges
- Apps Script 6-minute execution timeout: built checkpoint/resume system
- Strict formatting requirements for the ERP import (tab-delimited, specific date format)

Smart features:
- Thinking mode for better extraction accuracy on complex invoices
- Save responses from both models for comparison and debugging
- Audit script: recursive scan with hash-based dedup and missing file diagnosis
- Per-status guidance in the dashboard UI
- Fallback chains for required lookup fields

This went from 'just parse some PDFs' to a full accounts-payable automation.
Scope creep is real but the end result saves hours of manual data entry.

